<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I remember hunting in KC, although I never did it much as my cleric except the basement.<br>
<br>
1. Gems do not drop in KC.  So everyone bringing up OS and how much clerics make there needs to wake up, because if you are hunting in KC it probably means you are too low to get a group in OS with all the 60 clerics there.<br>
<br>
2. My cleric was a bit of a twink, and even so, I was 2 stones from encumbered with no coin and no extra stuff on me for a very long time.  I remember how much it sucked very well.  I couldn't afford tink bags back then and I couldn't carry FS weapons around.   A single one encumbered me.  I was always bugging people for str buffs.  Also as an inkie I didn't have FV one zone away to run to when I needed to bank, OT is only two, but being encumbered meant not a fun run.  Not to mention hunting in KC meant no OT bank either for many.<br>
<br>
3. If you don't die then stfu.  There are plenty of times people bug me to go hunt somewhere super easy and then want a group aego.  I don't care anymore because I usually group only with guildies and the guild pays for my peridots, but back when they were all out of my own pocket you better believe that if I was doing some retardedly easy camp (like Velk's upper spiders with a full group) I would only peridot buff the crowd control and the tank, maybe the puller, nobody else.  I never used to buff myself with a symbol.<br>
<br>
